<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 24px;
        color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
      }
      table {
        max-width: 600px;
        padding: 0 12px 24px 12px;
        margin-left: auto;
        margin-right: auto;
      }
      tr {
        text-align: left;
      }
      hr {
        color: #2c3e50;
      }
      a {
        color: #ca3827;
      }
      a:link {
        color: #ca3827;
      }
      a:visited {
        color: #4c6259;
      }
      a:hover {
        color: #ca3827;
      }
      a:active {
        color: #ca3827;
      }
      .article-title {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: 22px;
        font-weight: bold;
        color: #2c3e50;
      }
      .text-centered {
        text-align: center;
      }
      .pb-s {
        padding-bottom: 12px;
      }
      .pb-m {
        padding-bottom: 24px;
      }
      .pb-l {
        padding-bottom: 48px;
      }
      .pb-xl {
        padding-bottom: 56px;
      }
      .color-main {
        color: #2c3e50;
      }
      .font-s {
        font-size: 12px;
      }
    </style>
    <title>AR Weekly</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <table class="text-centered">
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="text-centered">
            <img
              src="<%= @logo_url %>"
              alt="AR Weekly"
              width="100px"
              height="100px"
            />
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="text-centered font-s pb-xl">
            Issue #<%= @issue_number %>, <%= Timex.format!(@issue_date, "{D} {Mfull} {YYYY}") %>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-xl">
            Hello guys! This digest covers Augmented Reality related news between <%= Timex.format!(@issue_date_from, "{D} {Mfull}") %> and <%= Timex.format!(@issue_date_to, "{D} {Mfull}") %>. Enjoy!
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-m">
            <h1 class="article-title">
              Bose Audio Smartglasses Debut at Coachella Festival
            </h1>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-s">
            The Bose Frames are capable of making calls and listening to music. The festival organizer Goldenvoice has collaborated with Bose to add Audio AR features to the Coachella App. It's small steps like this that bring AR, in this case Audio AR, closer to consumers.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-l">
          Source:
          <a href='<%= ArWeeklyWeb.Router.Helpers.page_url(ArWeeklyWeb.Endpoint, :track_issue_link, ArWeekly.EmailService.arweekly_encode(to_string(@issue_number) <> "@@" <> @subscriber_email <> "@@" <> "https://www.mobilemarketer.com/news/bose-brings-audio-ar-shades-and-festival-content-to-coachella/552302")) %>'
              >https://www.mobilemarketer.com</a
            >
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-m">
            <h1 class="article-title">
              New Standard for Storage und Distribution of 360째 Videos
            </h1>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-s">
            The new standard MPEG-OMAF developed by Frauenhofer improves 360째 video streaming performance. While conventional 360째 videos are streamed in a fixed resolution, MPEG-OMAF enables 360째 videos with dynamic resolution per tile. Tiles where the user is currently looking are streamed in high resolution while tiles out of the users sight are streamed in low resolution.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-l">
          Source:
          <a href='<%= ArWeeklyWeb.Router.Helpers.page_url(ArWeeklyWeb.Endpoint, :track_issue_link, ArWeekly.EmailService.arweekly_encode(to_string(@issue_number) <> "@@" <> @subscriber_email <> "@@" <> "https://venturebeat.com/2019/04/17/fraunhofer-demonstrates-5g-virtual-reality-video-streaming-software")) %>'
              >https://venturebeat.com</a
            >
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-m">
            <h1 class="article-title">
              Web Based AR Advances with 8th Wall's Latest Update
            </h1>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-s">
            8th Wall Web is currently the most promising platform to build web based AR solutions. The latest update brings image targets, which enables 2D images to act as a marker. A core feature of 8th Wall Web is the on-device image detection and tracking. This means better tracking performance and security, as no camera data is sent up to a cloud.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-l">
          Source:
          <a href='<%= ArWeeklyWeb.Router.Helpers.page_url(ArWeeklyWeb.Endpoint, :track_issue_link, ArWeekly.EmailService.arweekly_encode(to_string(@issue_number) <> "@@" <> @subscriber_email <> "@@" <> "https://mobile-ar.reality.news/news/8th-wall-brings-image-targets-its-web-based-augmented-reality-platform-0196339")) %>'
              >https://mobile-ar.reality.news</a
            >
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-m">
            <h1 class="article-title">
              Pinterest App Averages 600 Million Visual Searches per Month
            </h1>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-s">
            Visual search is considered to be one of the most promising AR cases. Google Lens recognizes a billion products and according to ARtillery Intelligence, $6.1 billion in annual transaction value will flow through AR interfaces by 2022. Besides Google and Snapchat, Pinterest just unveiled itself as a player with a huge potential.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-l">
          Source:
          <a href='<%= ArWeeklyWeb.Router.Helpers.page_url(ArWeeklyWeb.Endpoint, :track_issue_link, ArWeekly.EmailService.arweekly_encode(to_string(@issue_number) <> "@@" <> @subscriber_email <> "@@" <> "https://arinsider.co/2019/04/15/data-point-of-the-week-600m-pinterest-visual-searches-per-month")) %>'
              >https://arinsider.co</a
            >
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-s">
            Suggestions or comments are more than welcome! Just reply to this
            email.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-xl">
            Thanks for reading<br />
            <span class="color-main"><strong>AR</strong>&nbsp;Weekly</span>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-m font-s">
            You receive this Email because you are subscribed to the AR Weekly
            Blog. Your next delivery is on <%= Timex.format!(@next_issue_date, "{D} {Mfull} {YYYY}") %>.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="font-s">
            <a href="<%= @unsubscribe_url %>">Unsubscribe</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;
            |&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="<%= @privacy_url %>">Privacy Policy</a
            >&nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="mailto:hello@ar-weekly.blog">hello@ar-weekly.blog</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://github.com/Domeee/ar-weekly">Source Code @ GitHub</a>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <img width="1px" height="1px" src="<%= @issue_tracking_url %>" alt="">
  </body>
</html>
